# diezypunto-web — Cursor Rules

## What is this
Landing page + catalog + AI search + quote builder for Diezypunto (merchandising corporativo B2B).
Standalone web app — the bot (kairos-merch-core) is a separate repo.

## Stack
- Next.js 16 (App Router), React 19, TypeScript (strict)
- Tailwind CSS v4 (inline, no CSS modules)
- Framer Motion (all animations)
- Zustand (state management, 2 stores)
- lucide-react (icons)
- Anthropic SDK (server-side AI search)
- Deploy: Vercel (auto-deploy from GitHub)

## Project structure
```
src/
  app/
    layout.tsx              — Server component. Metadata, Geist font
    client-layout.tsx       — "use client". Wraps Navbar, Footer, WhatsAppButton, QuoteCart
    page.tsx                — Home page (hero + search + sections)
    globals.css             — Tailwind theme + CSS custom properties
    catalogo/page.tsx       — Catalog with category filters
    catalogo/[category]/    — Category page
    producto/[id]/page.tsx  — Product detail
    presupuesto/page.tsx    — Quote builder page
    api/
      search/route.ts       — POST. AI search with Claude extraction + rate limiting
      search/refine/route.ts — POST. Refine search within session
      products/route.ts     — GET. Filter/paginate products
      products/[id]/route.ts — GET. Single product
      categories/route.ts   — GET. Category list
  components/
    search/    — SearchPrompt, SearchResults, SearchRefinement
    catalog/   — ProductCard, ProductGrid, CategoryFilter
    quote/     — QuoteCart, QuoteBuilder
    home/      — Hero sections, FAQ, Testimonials
    shared/    — Navbar, Footer, WhatsAppButton
  lib/
    api.ts         — fetchJSON<T> client wrapper
    types.ts       — ProductResult, SearchResponse, etc.
    stores/
      quote-store.ts   — Zustand + persist (localStorage)
      search-store.ts  — Zustand (ephemeral, session-based)
    engine/
      llm.ts       — Claude extraction (server-side only)
      products.ts  — Product data + filtering
      ranking.ts   — Search ranking logic
      rate-limit.ts — IP-based rate limiting (in-memory)
    data/          — Static product data
```

## Key patterns

### Components
- **Server components** by default (layout.tsx). Add `"use client"` only when needed (state, events, hooks, Framer Motion)
- Keep components small and focused (20-110 lines typical)
- Access Zustand via selectors: `useQuoteStore((s) => s.addItem)`

### Styling
- Tailwind v4 inline classes only — no CSS modules, no component libraries (no Shadcn, no MUI)
- Custom CSS vars in globals.css: `--accent: #59C6F2`, `--eco: #10b981`
- Font: Geist (via next/font/google)
- Responsive: use Tailwind breakpoints (`sm:`, `md:`, `lg:`)

### Animations
- Framer Motion for everything — no CSS animations
```tsx
<motion.div
  initial={{ opacity: 0, y: 8 }}
  animate={{ opacity: 1, y: 0 }}
  transition={{ duration: 0.3 }}
>
```
- Use `AnimatePresence` for enter/exit transitions

### Data fetching
- Client-side in `useEffect` or Zustand async methods
- `fetchJSON<T>(url, init)` wrapper in lib/api.ts
- API routes are thin wrappers — business logic in `src/lib/engine/`

### State management (Zustand)
1. **quote-store** — cart, persisted to localStorage. Methods: addItem, removeItem, updateQty, clearCart, totalItems
2. **search-store** — search session, ephemeral. Methods: search(query), refine(query), clear()

### API routes
- All in `src/app/api/*/route.ts` (App Router convention)
- Return `NextResponse.json(data)`
- Rate limiting on search endpoints (10 req/min per IP, in-memory Map)
- Search uses Claude for intent extraction (server-side, API key in env)

## Code style
- TypeScript strict mode
- Interfaces for all API responses and component props
- `type` over `interface` for simple shapes, `interface` for extendable contracts
- Named exports for components, default export for pages
- Icons: always from lucide-react

## Brand / Design
- Dark theme with premium feel (glass effects, glow borders)
- Accent: teal (#59C6F2)
- Eco badge: green (#10b981)
- Rounded corners: `rounded-xl` default
- Subtle shadows and transitions on hover

## What NOT to do
- Don't add component libraries (Shadcn, MUI, etc.) — custom Tailwind only
- Don't use CSS modules or styled-components
- Don't use getServerSideProps/getStaticProps — App Router only
- Don't put Claude API key in client code — server-side only (API routes)
- Don't use CSS animations — use Framer Motion
- Don't fetch in render — use useEffect or Zustand methods

## Environment variables
```
ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=sk-...  # Server-side only, for AI search
```

## Running
```bash
npm install
npm run dev        # http://localhost:3000
npm run build      # Production build
npm run lint       # ESLint
```

